2
00:00:05.920 --> 00:00:07.960
- Milady, look, that boy is saying goodbye to his family.

3
00:00:07.960 --> 00:00:10.140
He's leaving his entire life behind.

4
00:00:10.140 --> 00:00:12.140
- There's no other way, Kitty.

5
00:00:12.140 --> 00:00:14.680
Lukaku Fey knows our secret identities.

6
00:00:14.680 --> 00:00:16.180
- Are we really sure about that?

7
00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:18.180
Has he told you who you are?

8
00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:19.680
- Yes.

9
00:00:19.680 --> 00:00:20.940
- What about me?

10
00:00:20.940 --> 00:00:22.640
Did he tell you who I really am?

11
00:00:22.640 --> 00:00:23.820
- Of course not.

12
00:00:23.820 --> 00:00:25.020
I could never know who you are,

13
00:00:25.020 --> 00:00:27.180
just like you could never know who I am.

14
00:00:27.180 --> 00:00:29.020
- What if he's wrong about me?

15
00:00:29.020 --> 00:00:32.100
(somber piano music)

16
00:00:32.100 --> 00:00:44.600
- Klaus in.

17
00:00:44.600 --> 00:00:45.700
Hey, wait!

18
00:00:45.700 --> 00:00:47.340
Don't go, Luca!

19
00:00:47.340 --> 00:00:48.580
- I have to go.

20
00:00:48.580 --> 00:00:49.980
- Maybe you don't.

21
00:00:49.980 --> 00:00:51.480
You say you know Ladybug and can't know

22
00:00:51.480 --> 00:00:53.980
our secret identities, but how can you be sure?

23
00:00:53.980 --> 00:00:56.280
Maybe you're wrong and you're leaving for Brazil

24
00:00:56.280 --> 00:00:57.280
over nothing.

25
00:00:59.080 --> 00:01:01.720
- If I stay, I'll only make it harder for Monarch

26
00:01:01.720 --> 00:01:03.820
to be defeated by Ladybug and you.

27
00:01:03.820 --> 00:01:09.260
- Hey, you're not allowed to be here.

28
00:01:09.260 --> 00:01:10.700
- Luca, wait!

29
00:01:10.700 --> 00:01:12.460
- I have faith in you both, Adrian.

30
00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:13.460
I'll be back soon.

31
00:01:13.460 --> 00:01:22.580
- In the daytime, I'm Marinette.

32
00:01:22.580 --> 00:01:25.640
Just a normal girl with a normal life.

33
00:01:25.640 --> 00:01:28.920
But there's something about me that no one knows yet.

34
00:01:28.920 --> 00:01:30.640
'Cause I've got a secret.

35
00:01:30.640 --> 00:01:33.420
â™ª Miraculous, simply the best â™ª

36
00:01:33.420 --> 00:01:36.460
â™ª I'm to the best when things go wrong â™ª

37
00:01:36.460 --> 00:01:39.380
â™ª Miraculous, the luckiest â™ª

38
00:01:39.380 --> 00:01:42.460
â™ª The power of double waves so strong â™ª

39
00:01:42.460 --> 00:01:45.460
â™ª Miraculous â™ª

40
00:01:45.460 --> 00:01:48.060
â™ª Miraculous â™ª

41
00:01:48.060 --> 00:01:51.500
- Remember your promise, Marinette.

42
00:01:51.500 --> 00:01:53.740
- Adrian?

43
00:01:53.740 --> 00:01:57.400
- Ladybug, can you explain what really happened?

44
00:01:57.400 --> 00:01:59.080
- Fight took place at the famous fashion designer

45
00:01:59.080 --> 00:02:01.240
Gabriel Agrest in Monarch.

46
00:02:01.240 --> 00:02:02.080
- Marinette?

47
00:02:02.080 --> 00:02:07.780
- You know, you can tell me anything, Marinette.

48
00:02:07.780 --> 00:02:10.060
- I don't know how much longer I can do this.

49
00:02:10.060 --> 00:02:11.420
I lied to everyone, Luca.

50
00:02:11.420 --> 00:02:13.160
I told them that Gabriel Agrest was a hero,

51
00:02:13.160 --> 00:02:15.720
but the truth is, he was the supervillain.

52
00:02:15.720 --> 00:02:17.160
He was Monarch.

53
00:02:17.160 --> 00:02:18.100
- What?

54
00:02:18.100 --> 00:02:19.660
My father was Monarch?

55
00:02:19.660 --> 00:02:21.640
How could you hide this from me, Marinette?

56
00:02:21.640 --> 00:02:23.160
You lied to me!

57
00:02:23.160 --> 00:02:24.700
You and I are over!

58
00:02:24.700 --> 00:02:25.540
- No!

59
00:02:27.640 --> 00:02:30.200
(panting)

60
00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:31.940
- Another nightmare, Marinette?

61
00:02:31.940 --> 00:02:35.080
- Not at all, I slept like a log.

62
00:02:35.080 --> 00:02:36.940
I feel completely evilized.

63
00:02:36.940 --> 00:02:39.620
I mean, energized.

64
00:02:39.620 --> 00:02:41.960
- Are you really sure you're okay?

65
00:02:41.960 --> 00:02:43.080
- It's fine, I'll be fine.

66
00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:44.420
It's all gonna be wrong.

67
00:02:44.420 --> 00:02:45.480
I mean, all right.

68
00:02:45.480 --> 00:02:55.300
- Is everything okay, Adrian?

69
00:02:55.300 --> 00:02:56.660
You only ate the cheese.

70
00:02:57.500 --> 00:02:59.060
- I'm not that hungry, Natalie.

71
00:02:59.060 --> 00:03:02.880
- I understand.

72
00:03:02.880 --> 00:03:04.180
This morning's meeting is bound

73
00:03:04.180 --> 00:03:05.840
to bring up painful memories.

74
00:03:05.840 --> 00:03:07.800
I can go alone if you want.

75
00:03:07.800 --> 00:03:10.140
- Natalie, I'm his son, I have to go.

76
00:03:10.140 --> 00:03:12.520
Besides, Marinette will be there to support me.

77
00:03:12.520 --> 00:03:17.220
- Give Adrian a big kiss from me, okay?

78
00:03:17.220 --> 00:03:18.780
- Sure, and many more from Monarch.

79
00:03:18.780 --> 00:03:20.680
I mean, from me.

80
00:03:20.680 --> 00:03:22.120
Bye mom, de-evilize you later.

81
00:03:22.120 --> 00:03:23.160
- Huh?

82
00:03:23.160 --> 00:03:24.720
- See you later.

83
00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:25.560
Love you.

84
00:03:28.360 --> 00:03:30.060
(door creaking)

85
00:03:30.060 --> 00:03:31.840
- Say hi to Adrian for me.

86
00:03:31.840 --> 00:03:34.900
- Thanks for the chiquette sent to dad.

87
00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:36.100
I mean, Super Dad.

88
00:03:36.100 --> 00:03:37.540
- See you tonight, sweetheart.

89
00:03:37.540 --> 00:03:42.400
- Marinette, maybe you should consider telling Adrian

90
00:03:42.400 --> 00:03:43.580
the truth about his father.

91
00:03:43.580 --> 00:03:45.380
It's eating away at you.

92
00:03:45.380 --> 00:03:47.040
- No, I promised Monarch.

93
00:03:47.040 --> 00:03:49.680
I mean, Gabriel aggressed that I would say nothing.

94
00:03:49.680 --> 00:03:51.140
- If you keep mixing up your words,

95
00:03:51.140 --> 00:03:54.920
you'll end up telling him everything by accident.

96
00:03:54.920 --> 00:03:57.360
- You're right, Tiki, I have to focus.

97
00:03:57.360 --> 00:03:59.260
But don't worry, I got this.

98
00:03:59.260 --> 00:04:03.000
- Knock, knock.

99
00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:03.960
- Who's there?

100
00:04:03.960 --> 00:04:04.900
- Papa.

101
00:04:04.900 --> 00:04:05.740
- Papa who?

102
00:04:05.740 --> 00:04:06.740
- Papa Corn.

103
00:04:06.740 --> 00:04:09.500
- What's wrong, Adrian?

104
00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:11.840
You're as pale as a cannon bear rind.

105
00:04:11.840 --> 00:04:13.980
- And Cat Noir, I was supposed to stop Monarch,

106
00:04:13.980 --> 00:04:16.840
but instead my father sacrificed himself to defeat him.

107
00:04:16.840 --> 00:04:18.820
I can't believe he and the hero who saved the world

108
00:04:18.820 --> 00:04:20.020
are the same person.

109
00:04:20.020 --> 00:04:22.320
It's like I'm missing something key here to understand,

110
00:04:22.320 --> 00:04:23.720
like who he really was.

111
00:04:23.720 --> 00:04:26.780
- Ladybug already told you how it went down, didn't she?

112
00:04:26.780 --> 00:04:29.660
- Yes, but I can feel she's not telling me everything.

113
00:04:29.660 --> 00:04:32.900
If only I'd been there when she faced Monarch.

114
00:04:32.900 --> 00:04:34.600
Hold on, Plagg, you were there.

115
00:04:34.600 --> 00:04:36.160
You can tell me what really happened.

116
00:04:36.160 --> 00:04:37.900
- I was there, I was there.

117
00:04:37.900 --> 00:04:42.500
I was inside the black cat ring in a magical energy state,

118
00:04:42.500 --> 00:04:44.680
kind of like cheese in a fondue pot.

119
00:04:44.680 --> 00:04:47.480
Needless to say, things were a bit blurry.

120
00:04:47.480 --> 00:04:49.140
(knocking)

121
00:04:49.140 --> 00:04:50.220
- Come in.

122
00:04:50.220 --> 00:04:52.420
- Delivery of chouquettes and marinettes.

123
00:04:52.420 --> 00:04:53.520
- Just what I needed.

124
00:04:53.520 --> 00:04:55.820
- Are you talking about me or the chouquettes?

125
00:04:55.820 --> 00:04:57.420
(laughing)

126
00:04:57.420 --> 00:04:59.480
- Are you ready to deceive, I mean, leave?

127
00:04:59.480 --> 00:05:00.920
- I am now that you're here.

128
00:05:00.920 --> 00:05:06.260
- This is the proposal selected by the city of Paris

129
00:05:06.260 --> 00:05:09.660
to replace the vandalized statue honoring Gabriel Agrest.

130
00:05:09.660 --> 00:05:11.300
Similar to the previous proposal,

131
00:05:11.300 --> 00:05:13.600
this statue will be financed by Mrs. Tsurugi

132
00:05:13.600 --> 00:05:15.200
and Theo Barbeau will be in charge

133
00:05:15.200 --> 00:05:16.640
of creating the sculpture.

134
00:05:16.640 --> 00:05:18.680
- Upon reconsideration, the first statue

135
00:05:18.680 --> 00:05:20.640
at the Place de Vaux Square didn't do justice

136
00:05:20.640 --> 00:05:22.040
to your father's presence.

137
00:05:22.040 --> 00:05:24.340
This one will be erected right outside City Hall

138
00:05:24.340 --> 00:05:27.080
and will be more than 10 meters high.

139
00:05:27.080 --> 00:05:28.280
- 10 meters?

140
00:05:28.280 --> 00:05:30.120
That sounds pretty high, don't you think?

141
00:05:30.120 --> 00:05:31.580
- Of course not.

142
00:05:31.580 --> 00:05:32.860
Nothing's too high to illustrate

143
00:05:32.860 --> 00:05:34.920
the greatness of your father, Adrian,

144
00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:38.900
a man who was able to combine talent, presence, and courage.

145
00:05:38.900 --> 00:05:39.960
- You knew my father?

146
00:05:39.960 --> 00:05:41.100
- Of course.

147
00:05:41.100 --> 00:05:42.860
I worked with him on several occasions.

148
00:05:42.860 --> 00:05:44.660
He was like a mentor to me,

149
00:05:44.660 --> 00:05:47.100
a man who defeated evil and poor taste

150
00:05:47.100 --> 00:05:49.340
with his nimble fingers, a man who--

151
00:05:49.340 --> 00:05:52.180
- Who tried to stop me from loving Marinette.

152
00:05:52.180 --> 00:05:53.000
- Sorry?

153
00:05:53.880 --> 00:05:55.340
My father might have been a hero,

154
00:05:55.340 --> 00:05:56.940
but I think you're seeing him as greater

155
00:05:56.940 --> 00:05:58.340
than he really was.

156
00:05:58.340 --> 00:06:01.040
- Your moth--

157
00:06:01.040 --> 00:06:04.420
Dad, your dad did save Ladybug.

158
00:06:04.420 --> 00:06:07.320
- Don't you remember the taste of his pancakes, Marinette?

159
00:06:07.320 --> 00:06:09.260
As dry and rigid as him.

160
00:06:09.260 --> 00:06:13.160
- Are you telling me that he was also a good cook?

161
00:06:13.160 --> 00:06:15.160
Such a model father.

162
00:06:15.160 --> 00:06:17.300
- I'm sorry, I need to think about it.

163
00:06:17.300 --> 00:06:23.000
- What about my statue, all good?

164
00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:24.200
You agree to it?

165
00:06:24.200 --> 00:06:26.340
- We will get back to you with our answer.

166
00:06:26.340 --> 00:06:29.540
- Wait up!

167
00:06:29.540 --> 00:06:32.880
Adrian, what's going on?

168
00:06:32.880 --> 00:06:34.520
- Marinette, you knew my father.

169
00:06:34.520 --> 00:06:35.880
Can you believe that he could have been

170
00:06:35.880 --> 00:06:37.560
both the man who saved Paris and the man

171
00:06:37.560 --> 00:06:39.820
who tried to keep us from loving each other?

172
00:06:39.820 --> 00:06:43.260
- I'm sure he loved you in his own way.

173
00:06:43.260 --> 00:06:44.760
- Even though I loved him too,

174
00:06:44.760 --> 00:06:47.020
I can't just forget the harm he caused us.

175
00:06:47.020 --> 00:06:49.560
And now hearing the way everyone talks about him,

176
00:06:49.560 --> 00:06:51.660
I feel like they're talking about someone else.

177
00:06:51.660 --> 00:06:54.840
I refuse to see him the way everyone else does.

178
00:06:54.840 --> 00:06:56.700
Does that make me a bad son?

179
00:06:56.700 --> 00:06:58.340
- No, of course not.

180
00:06:58.340 --> 00:07:00.400
You've done nothing wrong.

181
00:07:00.400 --> 00:07:03.080
- If only I'd been there, maybe I could have saved him.

182
00:07:03.080 --> 00:07:06.620
- There's nothing you could have done.

183
00:07:06.620 --> 00:07:07.780
- How do you know that?

184
00:07:07.780 --> 00:07:09.520
Neither of us were there.

185
00:07:09.520 --> 00:07:11.960
- Adrian, I think-- - Let's go home, Adrian.

186
00:07:22.660 --> 00:07:24.860
- If you want, I can cancel my lyre lesson.

187
00:07:24.860 --> 00:07:26.360
I mean, guitar lesson.

188
00:07:26.360 --> 00:07:27.540
- No, no, go ahead.

189
00:07:27.540 --> 00:07:28.840
Say hi to Luca for me.

190
00:07:28.840 --> 00:07:39.920
- I can't take it anymore.

191
00:07:39.920 --> 00:07:42.280
We have to tell Adrian the truth.

192
00:07:42.280 --> 00:07:44.660
- Have you lost your mind?

193
00:07:44.660 --> 00:07:47.020
You want to tell him that you're Ladybug.

194
00:07:47.020 --> 00:07:48.180
- What do you mean?

195
00:07:48.180 --> 00:07:50.520
- Only Ladybug would know that Gabriel Agrest

196
00:07:50.520 --> 00:07:53.220
was a monarch, not Marinette Dupain Chang.

197
00:07:53.220 --> 00:07:55.800
- Well, I could tell him everything as Ladybug.

198
00:07:55.800 --> 00:07:58.700
- And let him figure out that I was monarch's accomplice?

199
00:07:58.700 --> 00:08:00.100
We have determined a truth.

200
00:08:00.100 --> 00:08:01.240
We're sticking to it.

201
00:08:01.240 --> 00:08:03.000
You need to grin and bear it, Marinette.

202
00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:04.340
It's too late to go back.

203
00:08:04.340 --> 00:08:08.680
- Everything okay, Natalie?

204
00:08:08.680 --> 00:08:10.240
- Yes, Marinette simply thought

205
00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:11.820
she lost the keys to her scooter.

206
00:08:19.820 --> 00:08:22.120
- Try strumming the strings with your fingers, Marinette.

207
00:08:22.120 --> 00:08:23.260
You don't need to hit them.

208
00:08:23.260 --> 00:08:26.360
- I swear I sounded better when I practiced yesterday.

209
00:08:26.360 --> 00:08:27.700
I'll akumatize again.

210
00:08:27.700 --> 00:08:28.760
Try again.

211
00:08:28.760 --> 00:08:30.300
I'll try again.

212
00:08:30.300 --> 00:08:31.460
- Bon dia, Marinette.

213
00:08:31.460 --> 00:08:32.460
How are you?

214
00:08:32.460 --> 00:08:33.300
- Hey, Rupay.

215
00:08:33.300 --> 00:08:34.140
Todo bien.

216
00:08:34.140 --> 00:08:34.960
Things are great.

217
00:08:34.960 --> 00:08:35.800
Why wouldn't they be?

218
00:08:35.800 --> 00:08:37.680
(laughing)

219
00:08:37.680 --> 00:08:38.840
- I'm going for a swim.

220
00:08:38.840 --> 00:08:44.040
- You two make such a cute couple.

221
00:08:44.040 --> 00:08:45.740
There's clearly a monarch.

222
00:08:45.740 --> 00:08:46.840
- Monarch?

223
00:08:46.840 --> 00:08:47.680
- A spark.

224
00:08:47.680 --> 00:08:50.180
I meant there's a spark.

225
00:08:50.180 --> 00:08:52.080
- You can talk to me if something's wrong,

226
00:08:52.080 --> 00:08:53.180
you know, Marinette.

227
00:08:53.180 --> 00:08:55.220
- No, that's the thing.

228
00:08:55.220 --> 00:08:56.520
I can't tell you.

229
00:08:56.520 --> 00:09:00.460
Unless, of course, I can totally tell you.

230
00:09:00.460 --> 00:09:01.460
I'll be right there.

231
00:09:01.460 --> 00:09:02.300
- What?

232
00:09:02.300 --> 00:09:03.800
Like now, in Brazil?

233
00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:05.900
- Yes, I'll be there in an hour and 14 minutes.

234
00:09:05.900 --> 00:09:06.740
Don't go anywhere.

235
00:09:06.740 --> 00:09:08.040
I'm on my way.

236
00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:09.600
- Shall we get breakfast?

237
00:09:09.600 --> 00:09:12.140
I could go for a big aÃ§aÃ­ bowl.

238
00:09:12.140 --> 00:09:13.200
- No, thank you.

239
00:09:13.200 --> 00:09:14.780
I'd rather be alone for a while.

240
00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:19.880
- Luca, I agreed to be your pretend girlfriend

241
00:09:19.880 --> 00:09:22.720
to put up the pretense, but if it's hurting you,

242
00:09:22.720 --> 00:09:24.020
don't you think it would be easier

243
00:09:24.020 --> 00:09:26.020
if you just told Marinette the truth?

244
00:09:26.020 --> 00:09:27.120
- I already tried.

245
00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:29.680
- And how did it go?

246
00:09:29.680 --> 00:09:34.860
- I'm sorry, I can't accept it.

247
00:09:34.860 --> 00:09:37.600
- What, but you're the only one I can entrust with it.

248
00:09:37.600 --> 00:09:39.300
- I'm heading back to Brazil, Marinette.

249
00:09:39.300 --> 00:09:41.260
- But monarch's been defeated.

250
00:09:41.260 --> 00:09:42.100
There's no need to go to--

251
00:09:42.100 --> 00:09:43.500
- There's a new butterfly villain.

252
00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:44.940
I don't want to risk being akumatized

253
00:09:44.940 --> 00:09:47.180
and revealing your and Cat Noir's secret identities.

254
00:09:47.180 --> 00:09:48.700
- This is crazy.

255
00:09:48.700 --> 00:09:50.540
Why would you get akumatized?

256
00:09:50.540 --> 00:09:56.240
- Sass, scales, slither.

257
00:09:56.240 --> 00:09:57.080
- What are you doing?

258
00:09:57.080 --> 00:09:59.720
- Marinette, the truth is I'm not leaving

259
00:09:59.720 --> 00:10:01.720
because of the new butterfly villain.

260
00:10:01.720 --> 00:10:03.460
- But then why are you leaving?

261
00:10:03.460 --> 00:10:06.120
- You and Adrienne finally listened to your inner melodies

262
00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:08.820
and today they're forming a beautiful symphony.

263
00:10:08.820 --> 00:10:10.620
I'm happy for you two,

264
00:10:10.620 --> 00:10:13.360
but I'm still in love with you, Marinette.

265
00:10:13.360 --> 00:10:15.300
You're so radiant, so strong.

266
00:10:15.300 --> 00:10:17.200
How could I stop loving you?

267
00:10:17.200 --> 00:10:19.500
If I stay, I'm scared this pain will turn the joy

268
00:10:19.500 --> 00:10:21.300
I feel about seeing you together into jealousy

269
00:10:21.300 --> 00:10:22.740
and ruin our friendship.

270
00:10:22.740 --> 00:10:24.380
That's why I'm leaving.

271
00:10:24.380 --> 00:10:25.200
- Luca.

272
00:10:25.200 --> 00:10:28.880
- It's gonna be hard being away from you.

273
00:10:28.880 --> 00:10:30.040
- Please stay.

274
00:10:30.040 --> 00:10:32.080
Adrienne and I will make sure not to be too close

275
00:10:32.080 --> 00:10:32.920
when you're around.

276
00:10:32.920 --> 00:10:36.160
Just please don't go.

277
00:10:36.160 --> 00:10:38.620
- I apologize in advance for what I'm about to do.

278
00:10:38.620 --> 00:10:39.960
- What are you about to do?

279
00:10:39.960 --> 00:10:43.220
- I'm about to lie to you for the good of the three of us.

280
00:10:44.720 --> 00:10:45.900
- No, don't do that.

281
00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:47.260
(glass shattering)

282
00:10:47.260 --> 00:10:49.140
Then why are you leaving?

283
00:10:49.140 --> 00:10:52.600
- Because I've met an awesome girl in Brazil.

284
00:10:52.600 --> 00:10:53.440
- You have?

285
00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:54.900
That's amazing.

286
00:10:54.900 --> 00:10:57.040
- I'll be your friend forever, Marinette.

287
00:10:57.040 --> 00:10:58.380
You can always count on me.

288
00:10:58.380 --> 00:11:07.180
- Luca, what did you tell Marinette?

289
00:11:07.180 --> 00:11:10.780
- I couldn't bring myself to tell her anything.

290
00:11:14.020 --> 00:11:15.960
- I'm sure you'll get there eventually.

291
00:11:15.960 --> 00:11:29.840
- Natalie, I've thought about it

292
00:11:29.840 --> 00:11:31.240
and I think I'd feel more comfortable

293
00:11:31.240 --> 00:11:32.600
if there were no statue.

294
00:11:32.600 --> 00:11:34.800
- Understood, I'll take care of it, Adrienne.

295
00:11:34.800 --> 00:11:40.040
Hello, Madam Mayor?

296
00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:44.460
- Power down.

297
00:11:44.460 --> 00:11:55.260
- Did something bad happen, Guardian?

298
00:11:55.260 --> 00:11:56.800
- No, Sass, I just need you to lend me

299
00:11:56.800 --> 00:11:59.200
your miraculous for a moment, Luca, please.

300
00:11:59.200 --> 00:12:06.840
Tiki, Sass, unify.

301
00:12:06.840 --> 00:12:10.640
- Marinette, tell me what's going on.

302
00:12:12.920 --> 00:12:17.020
- Luca, I lied to the entire world.

303
00:12:17.020 --> 00:12:19.560
Adrienne's father wasn't a hero.

304
00:12:19.560 --> 00:12:21.360
He was a monarch.

305
00:12:21.360 --> 00:12:23.920
He made me swear that I wouldn't say a thing

306
00:12:23.920 --> 00:12:25.560
so that Adrienne would think well of him

307
00:12:25.560 --> 00:12:27.720
in order to protect him, but now because of that,

308
00:12:27.720 --> 00:12:29.760
I'm having to lie to everyone.

309
00:12:29.760 --> 00:12:31.200
- Why did you do that?

310
00:12:31.200 --> 00:12:33.660
- Because I love Adrienne more than anything

311
00:12:33.660 --> 00:12:36.300
and he'd be in so much pain if he ever found out.

312
00:12:36.300 --> 00:12:37.700
He could get akumatized

313
00:12:37.700 --> 00:12:39.840
by the new holder of the Butterfly Miraculous

314
00:12:39.840 --> 00:12:43.580
and I'll never, ever, ever let anyone hurt him.

315
00:12:43.580 --> 00:12:46.440
I have to keep this promise and hide the truth from him,

316
00:12:46.440 --> 00:12:48.820
even if it burns my lips and my heart every day

317
00:12:48.820 --> 00:12:50.020
until the end of time.

318
00:12:50.020 --> 00:12:54.820
Do you think I did the right thing?

319
00:12:54.820 --> 00:12:57.320
- I don't know, Marinette, I'm gonna ask you something

320
00:12:57.320 --> 00:12:59.920
you'll probably find very strange with.

321
00:12:59.920 --> 00:13:02.060
Please let me borrow your miraculous.

322
00:13:02.060 --> 00:13:03.740
- What, why?

323
00:13:03.740 --> 00:13:05.140
- I know things that you don't

324
00:13:05.140 --> 00:13:07.360
and I'm probably the only one who can fix this.

325
00:13:07.360 --> 00:13:08.600
Give me your earrings.

326
00:13:08.600 --> 00:13:10.140
- No, no, tell me what you're gonna do

327
00:13:10.140 --> 00:13:11.340
and I'll take care of it myself.

328
00:13:11.340 --> 00:13:12.640
- Marinette, I love you.

329
00:13:12.640 --> 00:13:14.040
You're the strongest person I've ever met,

330
00:13:14.040 --> 00:13:16.040
but this time I'm the one who needs to protect you.

331
00:13:16.040 --> 00:13:17.080
You have to trust me.

332
00:13:17.080 --> 00:13:19.340
- I'm sorry, I never should have told you any of this.

333
00:13:19.340 --> 00:13:20.680
- No, Marinette, you don't understand.

334
00:13:20.680 --> 00:13:21.520
Give me your.

335
00:13:21.520 --> 00:13:24.660
Marinette, tell me what's going on.

336
00:13:24.660 --> 00:13:27.420
- Divide.

337
00:13:27.420 --> 00:13:36.560
Be happy with Irube, please.

338
00:13:36.560 --> 00:13:39.460
- You came all the way here just to tell me that?

339
00:13:39.460 --> 00:13:43.240
- Yes, and that you must never worry about me, okay?

340
00:13:43.240 --> 00:13:50.880
- What, but how can he refuse to have a statue

341
00:13:50.880 --> 00:13:53.520
of his own father, a worldwide hero?

342
00:13:53.520 --> 00:13:55.220
- He probably isn't ready yet.

343
00:13:55.220 --> 00:13:57.180
We need to give him time to grieve.

344
00:13:57.180 --> 00:14:00.660
- Such an unworthy son.

345
00:14:00.660 --> 00:14:02.960
He doesn't recognize his own father's talent.

346
00:14:02.960 --> 00:14:04.920
He doesn't recognize his legacy.

347
00:14:06.900 --> 00:14:09.820
(dramatic music)

348
00:14:09.820 --> 00:14:12.260
- Hello, forgive my intrusion,

349
00:14:12.260 --> 00:14:16.400
but your anger was so great that it called out to me.

350
00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:19.240
Is someone keeping you from honoring the great man

351
00:14:19.240 --> 00:14:20.540
Gabriel Agrest?

352
00:14:20.540 --> 00:14:23.680
- Yes, his ungrateful son, Adrian.

353
00:14:23.680 --> 00:14:27.120
- I propose we teach Adrian a valuable lesson.

354
00:14:27.120 --> 00:14:29.540
- It would be my honor.

355
00:14:29.540 --> 00:14:31.420
And what should I call you?

356
00:14:31.420 --> 00:14:34.860
- I have something in mind, but I wouldn't dare.

357
00:14:34.860 --> 00:14:36.220
- Please do.

358
00:14:36.220 --> 00:14:39.420
In that case, call me Mr. Agrest.

359
00:14:39.420 --> 00:14:45.300
- Adrian!

360
00:14:45.300 --> 00:14:49.240
- I win!

361
00:14:49.240 --> 00:14:50.060
(laughing)

362
00:14:50.060 --> 00:14:50.900
- Adrian!

363
00:14:50.900 --> 00:14:54.240
- Correct me if I'm wrong,

364
00:14:54.240 --> 00:14:57.040
but didn't you just turn down the building of this statue?

365
00:14:57.040 --> 00:15:04.320
Time to say the magic words, don't you think?

366
00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:06.420
- Adrian, get to safety.

367
00:15:06.420 --> 00:15:11.420
- Adrian, I'm bringing you back to City Hall.

368
00:15:11.420 --> 00:15:14.120
You're going to agree to the building of my statue

369
00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:16.300
and recognize my brilliance.

370
00:15:16.300 --> 00:15:19.940
- Natalie!

371
00:15:19.940 --> 00:15:23.240
- Natalie's in danger.

372
00:15:23.240 --> 00:15:24.400
Plagg, claws out!

373
00:15:24.400 --> 00:15:29.080
Cataclysm!

374
00:15:34.380 --> 00:15:35.620
- Adrian is still inside.

375
00:15:35.620 --> 00:15:36.540
- I'll take care of him.

376
00:15:36.540 --> 00:15:37.380
Get to safety.

377
00:15:37.380 --> 00:15:42.660
- Seize Cat Noir's miraculous.

378
00:15:42.660 --> 00:15:44.260
- You bring it back to me

379
00:15:44.260 --> 00:15:46.360
and I'll explain how you can use it

380
00:15:46.360 --> 00:15:50.300
to make a wish to bring Gabriel Agrest back, for example.

381
00:15:50.300 --> 00:15:51.120
- What?

382
00:15:51.120 --> 00:15:51.960
I can do that?

383
00:15:51.960 --> 00:15:57.400
- You want to stop me from playing my role as a father, Cat?

384
00:15:57.400 --> 00:16:00.980
- You're, you're no one's father!

385
00:16:04.780 --> 00:16:05.620
Cataclysm!

386
00:16:05.620 --> 00:16:09.680
- You're just a giant talking statue.

387
00:16:09.680 --> 00:16:13.220
- Who are you to judge me, you tiny insignificant creature?

388
00:16:13.220 --> 00:16:25.400
Cataclysm!

389
00:16:25.400 --> 00:16:30.440
- No, no, I'm sorry, I didn't mean to cataclysm you.

390
00:16:30.440 --> 00:16:33.880
- Did you just try to destroy me, huh?

391
00:16:33.880 --> 00:16:35.380
- It really is just a statue.

392
00:16:35.380 --> 00:16:36.880
Whoever this akumatized villain is,

393
00:16:36.880 --> 00:16:38.180
he's hiding inside.

394
00:16:38.180 --> 00:16:39.020
Cataclysm!

395
00:16:39.020 --> 00:16:44.620
- If you want to be spared, help me find the Agrest's son.

396
00:16:44.620 --> 00:16:45.460
- Never.

397
00:16:45.460 --> 00:16:54.760
- I could really use a helping paw right now, m'lady.

398
00:17:04.280 --> 00:17:06.520
(grunting)

399
00:17:06.520 --> 00:17:13.360
- No one will stand between me and my son.

400
00:17:13.360 --> 00:17:18.760
Cataclysm!

401
00:17:18.760 --> 00:17:28.500
- Now, seize his miraculous.

402
00:17:34.880 --> 00:17:37.340
(hissing)

403
00:17:37.340 --> 00:17:38.180
- No!

404
00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:39.380
- Clear away the rumble.

405
00:17:39.380 --> 00:17:41.920
I want to see who was hiding beneath the mask.

406
00:17:41.920 --> 00:17:55.220
- Mr. Agrest?

407
00:17:55.220 --> 00:17:57.160
- Put the miraculous somewhere safe.

408
00:17:57.160 --> 00:18:03.500
- What did you do to Cat Noir?

409
00:18:04.740 --> 00:18:06.180
- She's vulnerable without a partner.

410
00:18:06.180 --> 00:18:07.400
This is your chance.

411
00:18:07.400 --> 00:18:11.920
(upbeat music)

412
00:18:33.880 --> 00:18:36.040
(hissing)

413
00:18:36.040 --> 00:18:45.580
- Is he invincible or something?

414
00:18:45.580 --> 00:18:46.420
Lucky charm!

415
00:18:46.420 --> 00:18:51.520
Lucky charm!

416
00:18:51.520 --> 00:18:55.320
Lucky charm!

417
00:18:55.320 --> 00:18:58.360
What am I supposed to do with all these?

418
00:18:58.360 --> 00:19:02.600
- Go ahead, take off your earrings.

419
00:19:02.600 --> 00:19:04.140
I want to see who Ladybug is.

420
00:19:04.140 --> 00:19:06.740
- Oh no, no!

421
00:19:06.740 --> 00:19:12.340
- Leave her alone!

422
00:19:12.340 --> 00:19:16.480
- Hadrian!

423
00:19:16.480 --> 00:19:18.720
- Who cares, seize Ladybug's earrings now!

424
00:19:18.720 --> 00:19:20.380
- First, I have to talk some sense

425
00:19:20.380 --> 00:19:22.620
into this unworthy son.

426
00:19:22.620 --> 00:19:24.960
- Education first, I understand.

427
00:19:24.960 --> 00:19:26.820
- But remember that we have a deal.

428
00:19:31.520 --> 00:19:32.820
- You are such a good father,

429
00:19:32.820 --> 00:19:34.960
then why didn't you want me to have any friends?

430
00:19:34.960 --> 00:19:37.100
- Huh, you don't know what you're saying,

431
00:19:37.100 --> 00:19:39.040
you ungrateful son.

432
00:19:39.040 --> 00:19:41.700
- Of course, how did I not figure it out sooner?

433
00:19:41.700 --> 00:19:44.280
Hadrian Agrest, use the megaphone on the ground!

434
00:19:44.280 --> 00:19:47.840
- Why did you want to control my every move?

435
00:19:47.840 --> 00:19:49.180
- What are you talking about?

436
00:19:49.180 --> 00:19:51.020
- Why were you always traveling around the world

437
00:19:51.020 --> 00:19:53.320
instead of staying with mom while she was sick?

438
00:19:53.320 --> 00:19:57.080
Why didn't you want me to meet my grandparents?

439
00:19:57.080 --> 00:20:00.820
- I, I didn't, he couldn't be like that.

440
00:20:00.820 --> 00:20:02.520
- Why didn't you want me to go to school

441
00:20:02.520 --> 00:20:03.820
like everyone else?

442
00:20:03.820 --> 00:20:06.400
Why didn't you want me to be in love with Marinette?

443
00:20:06.400 --> 00:20:10.000
- You're lying, you're talking nonsense.

444
00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:13.840
- Why did you stop being popcorn and become this,

445
00:20:13.840 --> 00:20:20.440
a cold, heartless statue?

446
00:20:29.920 --> 00:20:32.260
(screaming)

447
00:20:32.260 --> 00:20:44.000
- Miraculous Ladybug!

448
00:20:44.000 --> 00:20:54.840
- What have I done?

449
00:21:00.120 --> 00:21:02.180
- Sometimes, it's better to put ideas

450
00:21:02.180 --> 00:21:04.360
rather than people on a pedestal.

451
00:21:04.360 --> 00:21:06.620
For you never truly know someone.

452
00:21:06.620 --> 00:21:08.920
This magical charm will help you remember that.

453
00:21:08.920 --> 00:21:16.840
You know what you have to do,

454
00:21:16.840 --> 00:21:18.640
hurry and take it back to Cat Noir.

455
00:21:18.640 --> 00:21:26.440
Thank you, Adrian.

456
00:21:26.440 --> 00:21:28.120
You've shown a great deal of courage

457
00:21:28.120 --> 00:21:30.120
and I wouldn't have made it without you.

458
00:21:30.120 --> 00:21:36.820
- Found it. - Found it.

459
00:21:36.820 --> 00:21:41.920
- Good thing you were there, m'lady.

460
00:21:41.920 --> 00:21:44.460
I wasn't at the top of my game today.

461
00:21:44.460 --> 00:21:47.160
- That's why we're always here for each other, kitty cat.

462
00:21:58.480 --> 00:22:01.340
(grunting)

463
00:22:01.340 --> 00:22:02.180
Claws in.

464
00:22:02.180 --> 00:22:06.960
- At least you got to tell that statue how you feel.

465
00:22:06.960 --> 00:22:09.080
- It won't bring my father back

466
00:22:09.080 --> 00:22:11.760
and it won't help me figure out who he was either.

467
00:22:11.760 --> 00:22:14.560
I guess I'm gonna have to live with unanswered questions.

468
00:22:14.560 --> 00:22:17.740
- Spot's off.

469
00:22:28.680 --> 00:22:31.080
(phone ringing)

470
00:22:31.080 --> 00:22:33.620
- I saw what happened at your place, are you okay?

471
00:22:33.620 --> 00:22:36.780
- Everything's back in order, Marinette, I'm fine, thank you.

472
00:22:36.780 --> 00:22:37.620
- Are you sure?

473
00:22:37.620 --> 00:22:40.860
I mean, seeing your father again, it must have been--

474
00:22:40.860 --> 00:22:42.620
- He was just an akumatized villain.

475
00:22:42.620 --> 00:22:44.700
I'm going to be fine, really.

476
00:22:44.700 --> 00:22:46.960
- Okay, then good night.

477
00:22:46.960 --> 00:22:48.100
- Good night, Marinette.

478
00:22:48.100 --> 00:22:53.540
- At least you're no longer mixing up your words, Marinette.

479
00:22:53.540 --> 00:22:55.500
- I don't have a choice, either I keep it together

480
00:22:55.500 --> 00:22:57.700
or everything will fall apart.

481
00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:01.740
- Natalie was right, it's too late to go back now.

482
00:23:01.740 --> 00:23:14.960
Power down.

483
00:23:14.960 --> 00:23:25.800
- Luca Knows Ladybug?

484
00:23:25.800 --> 00:23:28.400
- Do you think he holds him miraculous?

485
00:23:28.400 --> 00:23:29.940
- I don't know, Manoey,

486
00:23:29.940 --> 00:23:32.540
but Luca definitely loves having secrets.
